Object.Field: LKM Hyperion Essbase DATA to SQL

Author: Oracle Version: 9.3.1.1 Last update: Oct 18th 2007
Description: - This is a load knowledge module that extracts hyperion essbase data and loads to the staging area.

Defines if report script, MDX query or Calculation script is used as extraction query. User has to provide a valid extraction query which fetches all the data to fill the output columns. The first record (first two records in case of calc script) should have the meta information of the extracted data.
There are three possible values for this option - ReportScript - MDXQuery - CalcScript
Fully qualified file name of the extraction query to be used for data extraction.

The column delimiter that has been used in the extraction query.
If nothing is specified in this option then space (' ') would be considered as column delimiter.
(Optional) Name of the Calculation Script to be run before extracting data from the cube.
MAXL script to be executed BEFORE extracting data from Essbase cube.
MAXL script to be executed AFTER extracting data from Essbase cube.
This option would be applicable only if user specifies PRE_EXTRACT_MAXL script. Aborts the extract process on encountering any error while executing pre-maxl script.
Data file location in calc script
This option would be applicable only if the query type is specified as CalcScript. The fully qualified extracted data file location where the data is extracted through the calculation script.
If this option is set to Yes, then logging is performed to the file specified by the LOG_FILE_NAME option.
The maximum number of allowed error

By default, this value is zero, which means that it will ignore any errors that occurs during the extract and load process into the staging area table. If this is set to a value greater than zero, then, the extract process that loads into the staging table will stop with an error once it reaches the specified number of errors.

By default, this value is zero, which means that it will ignore any errors that occurs during the extract and load process into the staging area table. If this is set to a value greater than zero, then, the extract process that loads into the staging table will stop with an error once it reaches the specified number of errors.
If this option is set to "Yes", error records are logged to a file specified by the ERROR_LOG_FILE name option.
If this option is set to Yes, then error records are logged to the file specified by the ERROR_LOG_FILENAME option.
Specify the name of the file into which the error records should be logged.
The column delimiter for error file
The column delimiter to be used for the error records file.
The row delimiter for error file
The row delimiter to be used for the error records file.
The text delimiter for error file

The text delimiter to be used for the column data in the error records file. For e.g, if the text delimiter is set as ' " ' (double quote), then all the columns in the error records file will be delimited by double quotes.
Flag to log the header row
If this option is set to Yes, then the header row containing the column names is logged to the error records file.
Set this option to NO if you wish to retain temporary objects (tables, files and scripts) after integration. Useful for debugging.

from java.util import HashMap from java.util import Map from java.lang import Boolean from java.lang import Integer from com.hyperion.odi.common import ODIConstants from com.hyperion.odi.connection import HypAppConnectionFactory from com.hyperion.odi.essbase import ODIEssbaseDataReader
# # Source Essbase Application connection properties #
serverName = "<%=snpRef.getInfo("SRC_DSERV_NAME")%>" userName = "<%=snpRef.getInfo("SRC_USER_NAME")%>" password = "<%=snpRef.getInfo("SRC_PASS")%>" application = "<%=snpRef.getInfo("SRC_CATALOG")%>" database = "<%=snpRef.getInfo("SRC_SCHEMA")%>"
portStr = "1423" srvportParts = serverName.split(':',2) srvStr = srvportParts[0]
if(len(srvportParts) > 1): portStr = srvportParts[1]
# # Put the connection properites and initialize the HFM App Reader # srcProps = HashMap() srcProps.put(ODIConstants.SERVER,srvStr) srcProps.put(ODIConstants.PORT,portStr) srcProps.put(ODIConstants.USER,userName) srcProps.put(ODIConstants.PASSWORD,password) srcProps.put(ODIConstants.APPLICATION_NAME,application) srcProps.put(ODIConstants.DATABASE_NAME,database) srcProps.put(ODIConstants.READER_TYPE,"DATA_READER")
print "Initalizing the Essbase App Reader and connecting" essbaseAppReader = HypAppConnectionFactory.getAppReader(HypAppConnectionFactory.APP_ESSBASE, srcProps);
# # Get the connection properties for the staging database # connection = snpRef.getJDBCConnection("DEST") stagingTableName = '<%=snpRef.getTable("L", "COLL_NAME", "W")%>' stagCols = '<%=odiRef.getColList("", "[CX_COL_NAME]=[COL_NAME] ", ", ", "", "")%>'
print "Staging Columns %s" % stagCols
# #extract the LKM Options # logEnabled = <%=snpRef.getOption("LOG_ENABLED")%> logFileName = r"<%=snpRef.getOption("LOG_FILE_NAME")%>" abortOnPreMaxlError = <%=snpRef.getOption("ABORT_ON_PRE_MAXL_ERROR")%> preMaxl = r"<%=snpRef.getOption("PRE_EXTRACT_MAXL")%>" postMaxl = r"<%=snpRef.getOption("POST_EXTRACT_MAXL")%>" extractionType = "<%=snpRef.getOption("EXTRACTION_QUERY_TYPE")%>" extractionQuery = r"<%=snpRef.getOption("EXTRACTION_QUERY_FILE")%>" colDelimiter = "<%=snpRef.getOption("EXT_COL_DELIMITER")%>" dataFileInCalc = r"<%=snpRef.getOption("EXTRACT_DATA_FILE_IN_CALC_SCRIPT")%>" preCalcScript = r"<%=snpRef.getOption("PRE_CALCULATION_SCRIPT")%>"
# error record handling maxErrors = <%=snpRef.getOption("MAXIMUM_ERRORS_ALLOWED")%> logErrors = <%=snpRef.getOption("LOG_ERRORS")%> errFileName = r"<%=snpRef.getOption("ERROR_LOG_FILENAME")%>" errColDelimiter = r"<%=snpRef.getOption("ERR_COL_DELIMITER")%>" errRowDelimiter = r"<%=snpRef.getOption("ERR_ROW_DELIMITER")%>" errTextDelimiter = "<%=snpRef.getOption("ERR_TEXT_DELIMITER")%>" logHeader = <%=snpRef.getOption("ERR_LOG_HEADER_ROW")%>
#set the extract options extractOptions = HashMap()
#generic ODI Knowledge module options extractOptions.put(ODIConstants.LOG_ENABLED, Boolean(logEnabled)) extractOptions.put(ODIConstants.LOG_FILE_NAME, logFileName) extractOptions.put(ODIConstants.ABORT_ON_PRE_MAXL_ERROR, Boolean(abortOnPreMaxlError)) extractOptions.put(ODIConstants.PRE_EXTRACT_MAXL, preMaxl) extractOptions.put(ODIConstants.POST_EXTRACT_MAXL, postMaxl) extractOptions.put(ODIConstants.EXTRACTION_QUERY_TYPE, extractionType) extractOptions.put(ODIConstants.EXTRACTION_QUERY_FILE, extractionQuery) extractOptions.put(ODIConstants.EXT_COL_DELIMITER, colDelimiter) extractOptions.put(ODIConstants.EXTRACT_DATA_FILE_IN_CALC_SCRIPT, dataFileInCalc) extractOptions.put(ODIConstants.PRE_CALCULATION_SCRIPT,preCalcScript)
#error record options extractOptions.put(ODIConstants.MAXIMUM_ERRORS_ALLOWED, Integer(maxErrors)) extractOptions.put(ODIConstants.LOG_ERRORS, Boolean(logErrors)) extractOptions.put(ODIConstants.ERROR_LOG_FILENAME, errFileName) extractOptions.put(ODIConstants.ERR_COL_DELIMITER, errColDelimiter) extractOptions.put(ODIConstants.ERR_ROW_DELIMITER, errRowDelimiter) extractOptions.put(ODIConstants.ERR_TEXT_DELIMITER, errTextDelimiter) extractOptions.put(ODIConstants.ERR_LOG_HEADER_ROW, Boolean(logHeader))
#Essbase specific load options extractOptions.put(ODIConstants.DATABASE_CONNECTION, connection) extractOptions.put(ODIConstants.MAPPED_COLUMN_NAMES, stagCols) extractOptions.put(ODIConstants.STAGING_TABLE_NAME,stagingTableName)
essbaseAppReader.beginExtract(extractOptions)
statString = stats.toString() raise "Essbase Data Extract Summary", statString
